<HR> <P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00135400000000000000> Scale Radius 1 Command</A></H2>
<P>
	<A NAME=est-sr1 HREF="est-sr1big.gif"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="" SRC="est-sr1.gif"></A>
	<A HREF="est-sr1big.gif">Figure (est-sr1): Scale Torus Radius 1</A>
<P>
<tt>mged&gt; <em>Select the ``edit menu'' entry in the solid edit menu</em> <BR>mged&gt; <em>Select the ``scale radius 1'' entry in the TORUS menu</em> <BR>mged&gt; <em>p 1.5</em> <BR>mged&gt;
</tt>
<P>
The distance from the vertex to the center of the cross-section of the
ring is set equal to the values given with <em>p</em>, eg, 1.5.
See 
	<A HREF="est-sr1big.gif">Figure (est-sr1)</A>
.
The original scale can be restored with
<P>
<tt>mged&gt; <em>p 1</em> <BR>mged&gt;
</tt>
<P>
<HR>

